IT Budget




Delta Apparel, Inc. along with its wholly owned subsidiaries, M.J. Soffe, LLC, Junkfood Clothing Company and To The Game, LLC, is an international design, manufacturing, sourcing and marketing company for branded and private label apparel. The company also operates Art… MoreDelta Apparel, Inc. along with its wholly owned subsidiaries, M.J. Soffe, LLC, Junkfood Clothing Company and To The Game, LLC, is an international design, manufacturing, sourcing and marketing company for branded and private label apparel. The company also operates Art Gun Technologies, which it acquired in 2009.
Delta Apparel, Inc. along with its wholly owned subsidiaries, M.J. Soffe, LLC, Junkfood Clothing Company and To The Game, LLC, is an international design, manufacturing, sourcing and marketing company for branded and private label apparel. The company also operates Art… MoreDelta Apparel, Inc. along with its wholly owned subsidiaries, M.J. Soffe, LLC, Junkfood Clothing Company and To The Game, LLC, is an international design, manufacturing, sourcing and marketing company for branded and private label apparel. The company also operates Art Gun Technologies, which it acquired in 2009.

Delta Apparel and its main subsidiary, M.J. Soffe, each have an IT department headed by a CIO and they operate independently of one another.

IT operations are primarily responsible for the maintenance and development of infrastructure and networking solutions at key domestic manufacturing sites, while also directing efforts at offshore manufacturing facilities in Mexico, Honduras and El Salvador. Additional focuses are application systems, business applications and workstation support. 

An eCommerce team focuses on Web development for its brand sites and business to client sites, and leads initiatives for developing new processes and implementing CRM initiatives. The company has integrated a new B2B Web store into its ERP system.

The company deploys IBM WebSphere Commerce, JBA System and DataWatch Monarch solutions.

Delta Apparel, Inc. has described cost as its biggest storage headache. Its top storage pain points are being routinely outside the backup window, data security, data loss.

Delta Apparel, Inc. uses disk backup across VTL SAN environment to back up its file data. It uses NetApp as its main backup application. Its daily and weekly total data backup is 8TB and 12TB respectively, with a 7-8 hour backup window. Its backup growth is around 1.2.

The IT budget is typically finalized in Q3.





